Students will be evaluated on the basis of (1) a group work assignments and (2) a final essay. The distribution of the final course grade is as follows:

- group work assignment (35% of the total grade);
- final essay (65% of the total grade);
- Kicking off the discussion for a seminar topic (no student can be eligible for a final grade without kicking off at least one seminar discussion - depending on the number of students enrolled)
- Class attendance (minimum in 5 of 7 seminars in order to be eligible for a final grade. Attendance in lectures is encouraged but not required).

Detailed information on each of the assignments is provided on the course's Moodle page.
